Pre-Game Insights: Equatorial Guinea have been flying high in terms of momentum in recent form. The team are unbeaten in the last eight matches in all competitions.
Liberia could not be in a worse situation coming into the match after five straight defeats including the loss against Malawi in the opener.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will take place at the Samuel Kanyon Doe Stadium.
The match will begin at 16:00 GMT on November 20, 2023.
Equatorial Guinea are the favourites to win the match.
Others: Liberia suffered a 1-0 loss against Malawi in the first group match while Equatorial Guinea received a huge boost in the qualification battle following a 1-0 success over Namibia just a few days ago.
Liberia are on the back of five consecutive losses and damage limitation will be the primary focus for the team.
Equatorial Guinea have not been without a big victory over the last few matches and it is unlikely to change in the upcoming match.
